<p>The economic case for solar in Honolulu is particularly compelling due to HECO's (Hawaiian Electric Company) electricity rates of 30.5¬¢/kWh, which are among the highest in the nation. For the city's 350,964 residents, many living in homes averaging 1,450 square feet, solar panels can provide substantial savings on monthly electricity bills. The tropical climate also means HVAC systems primarily focus on cooling and dehumidification rather than heating, allowing homeowners to optimize their energy systems for consistent year-round performance while taking advantage of Hawaii's net metering programs and solar incentives.</p>

